wardly available in both\nsimulations and data of galaxy velocity. Hence the sampling artifact in the\nvelocity power spectrum measurement can be self-calibrated within our\nframework. By applying such self-calibration in simulations, it becomes\npromising to determine the {\\it real} large scale velocity bias of\n$10^{13}M_\\odot$ halos with $\\sim 1$% accuracy, and that of lower mass halos by\nbetter accuracy. ...[abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Sep 2014 03:34:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 25 Sep 2014 01:24:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 9 Mar 2015 00:41:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-10"}
