n and similar recent four Stokes\nparameter magnetic mapping studies, we present a tentative evidence for the\nhypothesis that Ap stars with dipole-like fields are older than stars with\nmagnetic fields that have more small-scale structures. We find that our\nabundance maps are inconsistent with recent theoretical calculations of atomic\ndiffusion in presence of magnetic fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Sep 2014 13:33:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-01-14"}
